&lt;li&gt;Hands-on machine operation skills. The candidate should be comfortable operating high value equipment and computer-controlled tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The candidate will be comfortable delivering results in the face of adversity. When necessary, take action to find creative solutions and collaborate with experts/leaders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embrace a fast-paced startup environment, staying focused, self-directed, and eager to learn and adapt on the fly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge and responsibility for mechanical systems necessary to support AM operations including gas and fluid plumbing, shop floor equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to engage in manual support removal using air tools, part de-powdering in Solukon, and EDM operation for cutting parts off build plates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ownership of shop floor cleanliness and organization. The candidate must be able to learn from doing and work towards continuous process improvement by providing feedback and taking ownership of 5S activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintenance of equipment and supporting tools relevant to the manufacturing process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work safely while manipulating heavy objects and handling metal powders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The candidate will have strong knowledge of hand and power tools, how to use them to accomplish a given task.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Digital work order inputs/outputs, ability to follow computer-based directions and provide feedback to engineering staff for continuous improvement of process documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
