&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in designing, building, and testing of rocket engines, combustion devices, pumps, and valves&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional command of fundamentals, including compressible flow, thermodynamics, control systems, cryogenics, and instrumentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of data analysis and data processing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with operation and testing of pneumatic, hydraulic, and cryogenic fluid systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with aerospace standard fasteners, seals, tubing, fittings, and commercial off-the-shelf hardware&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with instrumentation including pressure transducers, thermocouples, accelerometers, and flow meters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in mechanical or aerospace engineering, or similar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willing to work in person in Moses Lake, Washington&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
