&lt;p&gt;As Security Manager, you will be responsible for all aspects of physical security, access control, security operations, emergency response coordination, and security infrastructure for Stoke’s Florida facilities. This position serves as the senior security leader for Stoke’s Cape Canaveral operations and ensures the protection of personnel, facilities, equipment, intellectual property, critical infrastructure, and company assets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will develop and execute site security strategies, manage contracted security personnel, oversee security technology systems, lead investigations, and serve as the primary liaison with federal, military, state, and local security stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with site leadership, facilities, operations, IT, environmental health and safety, and government partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who brings professionalism, sound judgment, novel solutions, and genuine commitment to safe operations. The pace here is fast and the stakes are high. You&#39;ll need to be calm under pressure, trustworthy, and lead by example from day one.&lt;/p&gt;
